Basic Education PS Belio Kipsang has said the government will implement the CBA it signed with teachers in recognition of essential services offered by the tutors with effect from July.He spoke on Friday at St Francis Girls Girls High School Mang&rsquo;u, where he represented Education CS Fred Matiang&rsquo;i during the schools Jubilee celebration. Kipsang said the government has invested Sh6 billion in the current financial year for infrastructure development in schools. The PS said President Uhuru Kenyatta puts a lot of importance to the education of Kenyan children. As part of that commitment to ensure all children have an equal opportunity, the government waived examination fees for students in both public and private schools.